  "style_summary_en": "Tabelog Japan #1 (4.72) — Kanazawa's pinnacle.\n\nChef Takuya Kataori personally visits mountains and fishing ports daily to source ingredients.\n'Subtractive cuisine' — a philosophy that listens to the inherent power of ingredients without elaborate technique or presentation.\nHokuriku Michelin 2-star.",
  "style_summary_jp": "食べログ日本1位（4.72）— 金沢の頂点。\n\n片折卓也シェフが毎日山・漁港を自ら回り食材を集める。\n「引き算の料理」— 華やかな技法・演出なく、食材本来の力に耳を傾ける美学。\n北陸ミシュラン2つ星。",
  "holistic_signature_en": "Kanazawa's pinnacle kaiseki.\nMinimalist cuisine under the chef's singular control, from sourcing to cooking.",
  "holistic_signature_jp": "金沢頂点級の懐石。\n食材集めから調理まで、シェフ1人が統制するミニマルな料理。"
